---------------------------------------------------------

11. Hardcoding

Hardcoding means assigning values directly while declaring
variables.

Example

int id = 10;

This is not recommended unless the value is common for all
objects.

---------------------------------------------------------

12. Common Data

If the data is common for every object, use static variables.

Example

private static String country = "India";

Every object shares the same value.

